replies.body:
Holy shit I fucking love this i take back EVERYTHINg i've said about the new lore.

My initial reaction to reading the PBE Bio was

{{sticker:sg-lux-2}} 

Because from the way it was worded, it seemed as if Zed was his own entity now who created the Order, but shared Kusho's sentiments about not using the Forbidden Magic. Like, he flat out REFUSED to use it during the war, and only did so out of pure desperation. It gave me a very faint tone reminding me of Varus' old lore, just without the vengeance, which I'm sorta 50/50 about. But it wasn't even the Varus tone that made me initially tilted, it was because it looked (to me, at least) as if you guys were gonna redo the Zed/Shen/Jhin story which I'd grown to love over my short year of playing this game, which worried me because that story, as well as Shurima's are my top two FAVORITE lores in the game.

But now that I have this knowledge... I'm starting to understand exactly what you guys meant in the short bio that was released. And I FUCKING LOVE IT. I kept telling some good friends of mine: "Holy shit they turned Zed into Ra's Al Ghul instead of Red Hood I want to fucking die", and now I have some amazing news to tell them. It feels as if I've been reborn. I can't wait for the full release of the story. 

{{sticker:sg-kiko}}

> Some vastaya tribes looking for a better deal, ally with the Noxus. 


"You were given Vastayan blood, yet chose to be blind"-{{champion:497}} 

IT ALL MAKES SENSE NOW! HOLY SHIT
